<hr size=3 width=50%>
<p>
<b>Regulations and Infrastructure: Labor and Employment
</b>
</center>
<P><ul>
<b>Books:</b>
<p>
<a href="/heritage/issues96/chpt5.html">Labor, Employment, and Wages</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/wilson.htm">D. Mark Wilson</a>.  (<i>Issues '96: The Candidate's Briefing Book</i>)<p>
<P>
<b>Policy Papers:</b>
<p>
<li>10/20/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/govern/bgup281.html">LIUNA, Organized Crime, and the Clinton Administration</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/weinstein.html">Kenneth R. Weinstein</a> and August Stofferahn. (Backgrounder Update #281)
<li>10/7/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/fyi121.html">Feeling the Pinch: Why Income Gains Remain Elusive for Many American Families</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/wilson.htm">Mark Wilson</a>. (F.Y.I. #121)
<li>10/4/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/govern/bg1094.html">From Meany to Sweeney: Labor's Leftward Tilt</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/weinstein.html">Kenneth R. Weinstein</a> and August Stofferahn. (Backgrounder #1094)
<li>9/1/96 <a href="/heritage/p_review/sept96/moloney.html">The Lady in Red Tape</a> by Sheila A. Moloney. (September-October 1996, Policy Review: The Journal of American Citizenship)
<li>8/5/96 <a href="http://www.heritage.org/heritage/library/categories/regulation/fyi115.html">High Layoffs and Long-Term Unemployment Cloud Jobs Picture</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/wilson.htm">Mark Wilson</a>. (F.Y.I. No. 115)

<li>7/31/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/govern/gip10.html">Organized Crime, Organized Labor, and Corruption of the Federal Grants Process</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/weinstein.html">Kenneth R. Weinstein</a>. (Government Integrity Project Report #10)


<li>7/18/96 <a href="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/bg1087.html">How Unions Deny Workers' Rights</a> by <a href="/heritage/staff/weinstein.html">Kenneth R. Weinstein</a> and Thomas M. Wielgus. (Backgrounder #1087)
